  <p>I hope we can work together no matter what the role is, but I'm at my best when
  the role looks something like the following:</p>
  <ul class="list margin--top-3">
    <li class="list__item list__item--good">
      You <strong><em>really</em> care about your customers</strong>, and building the
      best possible product for them.
    </li>
    <li class="list__item list__item--good">
      You <strong>value product design highly</strong>, and understand that is a
      company-wide value.
    </li>
    <li class="list__item list__item--good">
      You expect Engineering, Product &amp; Design to <strong>work very closely with
      each other</strong>.
    </li>
    <li class="list__item list__item--good">
      You expect Product to be <strong>deeply involved in execution</strong>: writing stories,
      planning sprints with engineering, etc.
    </li>
    <li class="list__item list__item--good">
      You're hiring for Head of Product, Director of Product or Senior Product Manager positions.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>You can <a href="/contact" class="link">get in touch with me</a> if you think
  I'm a good match for a position you have.</p>
</div>
